duties_responsibilities.duty: Support creating purpose-built solutions and technologies for delivering better health and human services outcomes.
Perform vital testing, troubleshooting, and analysis of application software for complex technical projects.
Design, develop, implement, maintain, and monitor critical test processes.
Gather requirements for testing, develop executable test cases and help distribute workload across a team of test engineers.
Coordinate and collaborate with others to analyze requirements and communicate defect-causing problems to stakeholders.
Assist in writing proposals to recommend process and programs for clients based on system capability assessments performed.
Prepare estimates for performing the various activities defined in the test plan.

education_certification.credential: Bachelor's degree in Software Engineering, Computer Science, or related field (Master's preferred)
